---
// §1 — the gap. Correct and aligned are two different bars, and the space
// between them is where misaligned diffs accumulate. Two-column contrast
// (same idiom as WhyWorkflow's manual/automated columns), a cost ledger for
// what the gap silently charges, and "the bet" — the project's stated reason
// to exist, set as a bordered aside.
---

<section id="why">
	<div class="container">
		<p class="kicker">§ the gap · correct <span class="thesis__arrow">→</span> aligned</p>
		<h2>Correct code isn't aligned code.</h2>
		<p class="thesis__lede">
			Output that compiles and passes tests can still be wrong for your
			codebase. Misaligned code isn&rsquo;t zero-value. It&rsquo;s
			negative-value: it ships, then it taxes every engineer who reads that
			file afterward.
		</p>

		<div class="thesis__cols">
			<div class="thesis__col">
				<p class="mono thesis__colHead">correct</p>
				<p class="thesis__colBody">
					It compiles. The tests pass. The diff looks fine in PR review.
					Every capable model produces this reliably today, at any price
					point. This bar is no longer the hard part.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="thesis__col">
				<p class="mono thesis__colHead thesis__colHead--aligned">aligned</p>
				<p class="thesis__colBody">
					It fits the codebase&rsquo;s existing patterns. It respects
					conventions that aren&rsquo;t written down anywhere. It makes the
					boring choices mature systems rely on, and it stays reviewable and
					extensible by the next person who touches it.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		{/* the two worlds, continued — columns pair vertically with the contrast
		    above: left = the correct-only world (without a driver), right = the
		    aligned world (with one in the loop) */}
		<div class="thesis-trade">
			<div class="thesis-trade__col thesis-trade__col--cost">
				<p class="mono thesis-trade__label">without a driver</p>
				<ul class="thesis-trade__list">
					<li>locally-correct, globally-misaligned diffs that pass review</li>
					<li>near-duplicates that cost the next refactor half a day</li>
					<li>architectural coherence eroding quietly, untraceable to any one diff</li>
					<li class="thesis-trade__answer">alignment debt is paid later, by someone else</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="thesis-trade__col thesis-trade__col--gain">
				<p class="mono thesis-trade__label">with the driver in the loop</p>
				<ul class="thesis-trade__list">
					<li>the pipeline asks the right questions at the right moments</li>
					<li>architectural decisions surface where they actually matter</li>
					<li>involvement is participation, not rubber-stamp approval</li>
					<li>review loops on hard data until the blockers read zero</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>

		<aside class="thesis__bet">
			<p class="mono thesis__betLabel">the bet</p>
			<p class="thesis__betBody">
				Models will keep getting better; that isn&rsquo;t the bet. The
				bet is that the structural conditions for fully autonomous coding are
				a decade-scale problem. For that whole interval, the realistic
				operating model is an experienced driver in the loop. rpiv-pi is the
				engine for that loop: it writes and verifies code under expert
				supervision, at LLM speed.
			</p>
		</aside>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.thesis__arrow { color: var(--ochre); }
	.thesis__lede {
		font-family: var(--font-serif);
		max-width: 60ch;
		color: var(--text-quiet);
		font-size: var(--type-lead);
		line-height: var(--leading-body);
		margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-7);
		text-wrap: pretty;
	}

	/* ── Two-column contrast ── */
	.thesis__cols {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: var(--space-6);
		max-width: 920px;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
	}
	.thesis__colHead {
		font-size: var(--type-small);
		color: var(--text-distant);
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
	}
	/* the right column is the "good" column in both rows of this section
	   (aligned above, with-the-driver below) — it carries the warm ochre
	   accent; the correct-only world on the left stays grey. */
	.thesis__colHead--aligned { color: var(--ochre); }
	.thesis__colBody {
		font-family: var(--font-serif);
		font-size: var(--type-base);
		line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
		color: var(--text-quiet);
		margin: 0;
		text-wrap: pretty;
	}

	/* ── Ledger — same idiom as the §why gain/cost trade ── */
	.thesis-trade {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: var(--space-6);
		max-width: 920px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
		padding-top: var(--space-5);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
	}
	.thesis-trade__label {
		font-size: var(--type-tiny);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
	}
	.thesis-trade__col--gain .thesis-trade__label { color: var(--ochre); }
	.thesis-trade__col--cost .thesis-trade__label { color: var(--text-distant); }
	.thesis-trade__list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-2);
	}
	.thesis-trade__list li {
		font-family: var(--font-serif);
		font-size: var(--type-small);
		line-height: var(--leading-snug);
		color: var(--text-quiet);
		padding-left: var(--space-4);
		position: relative;
	}
	.thesis-trade__col--gain .thesis-trade__list li::before {
		content: "+";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--ochre);
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
	}
	.thesis-trade__col--cost .thesis-trade__list li::before {
		content: "−";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--text-distant);
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
	}
	.thesis-trade__answer { color: var(--text-distant); font-style: italic; }
	.thesis-trade__col--cost .thesis-trade__answer::before { content: "↳"; }

	/* ── The bet — the thesis punchline, marked with the hanko square the
	   system stamps on significant moments (ScrollIndicator seal, Install) ── */
	.thesis__bet {
		max-width: 920px;
		border-left: 1px solid var(--ochre);
		padding: var(--space-2) 0 var(--space-2) var(--space-5);
	}
	.thesis__betLabel {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: var(--space-2);
		font-size: var(--type-tiny);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		color: var(--ochre);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
	}
	.thesis__betLabel::before {
		content: "";
		width: 9px;
		height: 9px;
		background: var(--ochre);
		transform: rotate(8deg);
		box-shadow:
			inset 0 0 0 0.5px color-mix(in oklab, var(--kuro) 60%, transparent),
			0 0 12px color-mix(in oklab, var(--ochre) 25%, transparent);
	}
	.thesis__betBody {
		font-family: var(--font-serif);
		font-size: var(--type-base);
		line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
		color: var(--text-quiet);
		margin: 0;
		max-width: 64ch;
		text-wrap: pretty;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.thesis__cols, .thesis-trade { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-5); }
	}
</style>
